workflow.name: Business AI command center: Modular agents for Google Workspace, vector search & multi-channel reports
workflow.description:
# üöÄ AI OPS Agent for n8n ‚Äî Stop Doing Busy Work. Start Leading. *Your AI workforce is ready. Are you?* ## üí∞ What You Get: Your ROI in 30 Days **Replace 10-15 hours/week of manual work** with intelligent automation that actually understands your business. While your competitors copy-paste data between tools, you'll be making strategic decisions. --- ## üß† The Powerhouse Stack That Does Everything | **Module** | **Core Job** | **Your Competitive Edge** | |------------|-------------|--------------------------| | **MAIN AGENT** (Grok 4) | Orchestrator & brain | ‚Ä¢ Reads your message ‚Üí builds execution plan
‚Ä¢ Delegates to specialized agents
‚Ä¢ Delivers results through your preferred channel | | **Knowledge Agent** | Company-wide research assistant | ‚Ä¢ Vector-searches your Supabase docs instantly
‚Ä¢ Runs live SQL queries for real-time numbers
‚Ä¢ Hunts & parses Drive files automatically
‚Ä¢ Pulls fresh web intelligence via Perplexity | | **Google Sheets MCP Toolkit** | Spreadsheet automation | **Natural-language control** over **read/append/update/clear/create/delete** operations on any tab or range | | **Google Drive MCP Toolkit** | File intelligence pipeline | ‚Ä¢ Auto-detects file types & extracts text from PDFs/CSVs
‚Ä¢ Transcribes audio/video content
‚Ä¢ Describes images with GPT-4o Mini | | **Vector Store Loader** | Long-term memory system | ‚Ä¢ Auto-chunks new files
‚Ä¢ Creates OpenAI embeddings
‚Ä¢ Stores in Supabase for instant semantic search | | **Postgres Chat Memory** | Conversation context | Never repeat yourself‚Äîevery follow-up question builds on previous context | | **Report Agent** | Executive briefing machine | ‚Ä¢ Converts raw outputs ‚Üí clean Markdown ‚Üí HTML
‚Ä¢ Auto-emails/Slacks/Telegrams polished reports | | **LinkedIn Scraper** | Talent & market intelligence | Scrapes full LinkedIn profiles via Apify, delivers structured JSON for analysis | | **Multi-Channel Triggers** | Meet users where they work | **Slack ‚Ä¢ Gmail ‚Ä¢ Telegram ‚Ä¢ WhatsApp ‚Ä¢ HTTP Webhooks** | | **LLM Layer** | Right model, right job | **Grok 4** (reasoning) ‚Ä¢ **Claude Sonnet 4** (analysis) ‚Ä¢ **GPT-4o Mini** (speed) ‚Ä¢ **Perplexity** (live web) | --- ## ‚ö° How It Works (The Magic in 5 Steps) 1. **Message arrives** (Slack mention, email, webhook) 2. **MAIN AGENT** analyzes ‚Üí selects optimal tool chain 3. **Specialized toolkits execute** (Sheets, Drive, SQL, Scraper...) 4. **Knowledge Agent** synthesizes everything using the perfect LLM 5. **Report Agent** packages & delivers results to your chosen channel --- ## üéØ Real Commands That Save Hours Daily > **"Update the Marketing-Spend sheet with last week's totals, then email me a chart."** > > **"Find the product-launch PDF from Drive, summarize key risks, post to Slack."** > > **"Scrape this LinkedIn URL, rank the candidate's skills, add them to our CRM sheet."** > > **"Create a new Sprint 11 tab, copy headers from Sprint 10, and ping the team."** *One command. Multiple systems. Zero manual work.* --- ## Why Choose This Over Other Products: ### ‚úÖ **All Your Data, One Brain** No more jumping between 12 different tools. Your AI agent connects everything. ### You can go further If you want to increase the Agent capabilities or make the more powerfull you can reach the dev. ### ‚úÖ **Vector Search Built-In** Upload a 100-page document once. Search it forever with natural language. ### ‚úÖ **Executive-Ready Reports** Your C-suite gets clean HTML briefs, not raw data dumps that waste their time. ### ‚úÖ **Deploy in Minutes** Plug into your existing n8n setup, add credentials, watch routine ops handle themselves. ---

nodes.name: Google Sheets - Read Data
nodes.notes:
üìä READ SPREADSHEET DATA

Retrieve and analyze data from Google Sheets. Perfect for AI to read, process, and extract insights from spreadsheet content.

Use Cases:
‚Ä¢ "Read data from the Sales sheet"
‚Ä¢ "Get all entries from A1:E100"
‚Ä¢ "Show me the data in the Budget spreadsheet"
‚Ä¢ "Extract customer information from the CRM sheet"

AI Parameters:
‚Ä¢ Document_ID: Target spreadsheet ID
‚Ä¢ Sheet_Name: Specific sheet tab name
‚Ä¢ Range: Cell range to read (optional)

nodes.name: Google Sheets - Clear Data
nodes.notes:
üóëÔ∏è CLEAR SPREADSHEET DATA

Remove data from specific ranges or entire sheets. Useful for resetting data, clearing temporary calculations, or preparing sheets for new data.

Use Cases:
‚Ä¢ "Clear all data from the temp sheet"
‚Ä¢ "Remove entries from A1:E100"
‚Ä¢ "Clean up the old data in column C"
‚Ä¢ "Reset the calculation area"

AI Parameters:
‚Ä¢ Document_ID: Target spreadsheet ID
‚Ä¢ Sheet_Name: Sheet to clear data from
‚Ä¢ Range: Specific range to clear

‚ö†Ô∏è Use with caution - data will be permanently removed!

nodes.name: Google Sheets - Add Data
nodes.notes:
‚ûï ADD NEW DATA

Append new rows of data to existing sheets. Perfect for adding records, logging events, or inserting new entries without affecting existing data.

Use Cases:
‚Ä¢ "Add a new customer to the CRM sheet"
‚Ä¢ "Log today's sales data"
‚Ä¢ "Insert a new project entry"
‚Ä¢ "Record the meeting notes"

AI Parameters:
‚Ä¢ Document_ID: Target spreadsheet ID
‚Ä¢ Sheet_Name: Sheet to add data to
‚Ä¢ Data_To_Add: Array/object of new data

Features:
‚Ä¢ Automatically finds next empty row
‚Ä¢ Preserves existing data
‚Ä¢ Supports multiple columns

nodes.name: Google Sheets - Create Sheet
nodes.notes:
üìã CREATE NEW SHEET

Create new worksheet tabs within existing spreadsheets. Great for organizing data into categories or creating project-specific sheets.

Use Cases:
‚Ä¢ "Create a new sheet called 'Q4 Sales'"
‚Ä¢ "Add a Project Timeline sheet"
‚Ä¢ "Make a new Budget 2024 tab"
‚Ä¢ "Create a sheet for customer feedback"

AI Parameters:
‚Ä¢ Document_ID: Target spreadsheet ID
‚Ä¢ New_Sheet_Name: Name for the new sheet
‚Ä¢ Header_Row: Optional column headers

Best Practices:
‚Ä¢ Use descriptive sheet names
‚Ä¢ Include header rows for data structure
‚Ä¢ Consider sheet organization strategy

nodes.name: Google Sheets - Update Data
nodes.notes:
‚úèÔ∏è UPDATE EXISTING DATA

Modify specific cells or ranges with new values. Perfect for updating records, correcting data, or maintaining current information.

Use Cases:
‚Ä¢ "Update the status in cell C5 to 'Complete'"
‚Ä¢ "Change the price in the product list"
‚Ä¢ "Modify the project deadline"
‚Ä¢ "Update customer contact information"

AI Parameters:
‚Ä¢ Document_ID: Target spreadsheet ID
‚Ä¢ Sheet_Name: Sheet containing data to update
‚Ä¢ Range: Specific cells to update (e.g., A1:B2)
‚Ä¢ New_Values: Array of new values

Tip: Use precise ranges to avoid overwriting unintended data

nodes.name: Google Sheets - Delete Sheet
nodes.notes:
üóëÔ∏è DELETE SHEET

Remove entire worksheet tabs when they're no longer needed. Use with caution as this permanently removes all data in the sheet.

Use Cases:
‚Ä¢ "Delete the old temp sheet"
‚Ä¢ "Remove the expired project tab"
‚Ä¢ "Clean up test worksheets"
‚Ä¢ "Delete duplicate sheets"

AI Parameters:
‚Ä¢ Document_ID: Target spreadsheet ID
‚Ä¢ Sheet_Name: Sheet tab to delete

‚ö†Ô∏è PERMANENT ACTION - Cannot be undone!
Always backup important data first.

nodes.name: MCP Server Sheets
nodes.notes:
üöÄ MCP TRIGGER

This is the entry point for AI interactions with Google Sheets. The MCP (Model Context Protocol) trigger allows AI models to call any of the connected Google Sheets tools based on user requests.

Key Features:
‚Ä¢ Enables natural language spreadsheet commands
‚Ä¢ Routes AI requests to appropriate Sheets operations
‚Ä¢ Provides context-aware data management
‚Ä¢ Supports complex multi-step data workflows
‚Ä¢ Handles dynamic sheet and document selection
